article.description: — Dameane Douglas posted 18 points and Loyola Marymount edged UC Irvine 51-48 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Douglas, Scott carry Loyola Marymount past UC Irvine 51-48
article.linkText: Douglas, Scott carry Loyola Marymount past UC Irvine 51-48
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- — Dameane Douglas posted 18 points and Loyola Marymount edged UC Irvine 51-48 on Thursday night. Douglas made a pair of free throws to stretch the Lions' lead to 50-41 with 2:11 to play. UCI's Jeron Artest made a 3-pointer and Justin Hohn a layup to pull to 50-48 with 38 seconds left. Collin Welp missed a 3-point shot for the Anteaters to end it. Eli Scott added 11 points for Loyola Marymount (4-3). Mattias Markusson chipped in seven points. Ivan Alipiev had seven rebounds. Dawson Baker had 12 points for the Anteaters (2-4). Welp added 11 points and 19 rebounds. Brad Greene had three blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ Elements of this were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
